The paper introduces a novel approach for online nonlinear regression using decision trees and second order methods. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of decision trees and adaptive partitioning also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses computational complexity issues, which could place it under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on performance and efficiency could also suggest a connection to systems and control (cs.SI).
